---
description: Design system rules (colors, typography, spacing, RTL) with performance-oriented Tailwind usage
globs: ["front/src/**/*.{js,jsx,css}", "front/tailwind.config.js"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Colors and tokens
  - Use Tailwind extended palettes from `front/tailwind.config.js`: `brand-red`, `brand-blue`, `accent-*`, `ui-*`, and `status-*` tokens.
  - Status colors: match tabs and badges—received: blue, inMaintenance: amber, completed: green, failed: red, sending: purple, returns: gray.
  - Returns sub-tabs: "سليمة" must use green semantics; "تالفة" must use red. Follow the styles in `OrderManagementPage` buttons.

- Typography and spacing
  - Fonts: `'Cairo Play'` primary, with `Cairo`/`Tajawal` fallbacks. Use Tailwind `fontFamily` tokens (`font-cairo`, `font-cairo-play`).
  - Use fluid `fontSize` and `spacing` scales defined in Tailwind config for responsive Arabic UI.

- RTL and dark mode
  - Default direction is RTL; use utilities added by the Tailwind plugin (e.g., `--start/--end`, `.rtl-space-x-reverse`).
  - Dark mode is class-based; toggle via `ThemeProvider`. Avoid inline colors when tokens suffice.

- Components and utilities
  - Prefer semantic utility compositions (e.g., `glass-effect`, `text-gradient`, `scan-frame`) already defined.
  - Keep interactive feedback subtle and performant: use Tailwind keyframes (`fade-in`, `slide-*`, `glow`, `shimmer`).

- Performance
  - Avoid deep selector chains; compose via utility classes.
  - Limit custom CSS in `index.css` to base/component layers; keep most styling within Tailwind utilities.

These rules preserve visual consistency and high performance while matching the current brand language.

